From: Glen Hadley <glenh@RSUN.INAV.NET>
Subject: Re: Old Brake Drums..

Well, I understand that an old drum makes a good charcoal fired forge.
Just hook up a hair dryer (without heat) to pump air through the hole in
the middle and you can get decent temperature out of it.  They say the
cast drums won't burn through.  Just a thought.  :<)


